Note: Auto attacks, Boosted attacks and Mean Look boosted attacks can critically strike but Umbreon has 0% base Critical-Hit rate at all levels. When on a team with four other eeveelutions, gains +1% maximum HP.

Eevee

Evolves At 4

Anticipation

Passive Ability

When Eevee would be shoved, thrown or left unabled to act, that effect is negated. This effect goes on a 40s cooldown after being triggered and is reset after respawning.

Inner Focus

Passive Ability

When Umbreon would be shoved, thrown or left unabled to act, that effect is negated. Umbreon becomes unstoppable for 1.2s afterwards and also its Defense and Sp. Def are increased by 30% for 3s. This effect goes on a 40s cooldown after being triggered and is reset after respawning.

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack every third attack, lunging at a Pokémon and dealing damage. This boosted attack also heals the user's HP. The lower the user's remaining HP, the more HP is restored.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

140% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

Swift

Move 1

6.00s Buff

Shoot 1 large and 3 small star-shaped rays, dealing damage to Pokémon and applying a mark to them after the fourth star hits that lasts 4s. When near a marked Pokémon, Eevee receives a 15% movement speed increase. When Eevee deals damage to a marked Pokémon, its next basic attack becomes a boosted attack.

40% Atk + 10 x (Level - 1) + 100

12% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 30

Swift Upgrade Choices

Mean Look

9.00s Hindrance

Pins an enemy Pokémon with a dark, arresting look, slowing them by 30% for 2s. After a 0.5s delay, the enemy is surrounded by a black zone they cannot leave for 3s. While inside the black zone, Umbreon’s basic attacks become boosted and deal increased damage. The black zone is removed if the target enemy is knocked out.

Mean Look is cleansable if the cleanse is used when the laser connects and before the area appears on the ground.

196% Atk + 5 x (Level - 1) + 180

Increases the duration of the black zone to 3.5s.

Foul Play

7.00s Dash

Charges in a direction, dealing damage to Pokémon hit and slowing them by 15% for 2.5s. If the charge hits a Pokémon, this move can be used again within 6s and it will note the highest Attack stat of all enemies hit. If this move is used again, Umbreon sweeps in front of itself with its tail, dealing damage to Pokémon hit, slowing them by 30% for 2.5s and shoving them for 1s. If the highest enemy Attack was greater than Umbreon's Attack when the first stage hit, the second stage deals damage using the noted Attack. Otherwise it uses Umbreon's current Attack.

64% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 160

Umbreon's next basic attack after using this move becomes a boosted attack.

Fake Tears

Move 2

8.00s Area

Feigns crying, dealing damage to nearby Pokémon and decreases their Defense and Sp. Def by 20% for 2s. Also grants a shield for 4s.

86% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 240

Fake Tears Upgrade Choices

Wish

6.00s Recovery

Wishes for an ally Pokémon or Umbreon. For 2s, that Pokémon receives 15% reduced damage, then afterward, the wish comes true and heals them. If the targeted Pokémon is knocked out before the wish comes true, a different ally Pokémon near them takes the wish instead.

300% Atk + 18 x (Level - 1) + 600

Increases the damage reduction to 25% and amount of healing when the wish comes true.

380% Atk + 18 x (Level - 1) + 700

Snarl

10.00s Debuff

Becomes hindrance resistant and begin snarling for 1.5s, dealing damage to enemy Pokémon in the area around Umbreon and decreasing the affected Pokémon's Attack and Sp. Atk stat by 3% for 1.5s and movement speed by 15% for 2s. Also grants the user a shield for 2s. Umbreon is slowed by 30% while snarling. The final shout leaves enemy Pokémon stunned for 0.7s and further decreases their Attack and Sp. Atk by 15% for 3s. The small shout Attack and Sp. Atk decreases can stack up to 6 times and stack with the big shout's Attack and Sp. Atk decreases.

15% Atk + 1 x (Level - 1) + 40

30% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 80

Increases the stun duration of the final shout to 1s.

Moonlight Prance

Unite Move

112s 100000 Debuff

Unlocks at level 8

Umbreon briefly becomes unstoppable, leaping up and absorbing the shields of enemy Pokémon in the area around Umbreon, taking them for the user. Umbreon then lands, dealing damage to Pokémon in an area-of-effect, and stuns them for 1s. For 5s, enemy Pokémon in the area around Umbreon are slowed by 30%, and if an enemy Pokémon in that area is granted a shield, Umbreon absorbs 50% of the shield for themself. Additionally, after learning this move and while not in combat, Umbreon continually recovers 1% Max HP every second.

Note: Umbreon cannot steal shields granted by Rayquaza or Assault Vest.

224% Atk + 13 x (Level - 1) + 630

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 10% Max HP Shield
